AGI - "I am honored to announce today the participation of Pope Francis in the work of the G7 in the session dedicated to artificial intelligence". Thus the President of the Council Giorgia Meloni in a video in which he illustrates the themes that will be addressed by the Italian Presidency of the G7.
<div </div
&nbsp;
"I cordially thank the Holy Father for accepting the invitation of Italy. His presence - Meloni again emphasizes - gives prestige to our nation and the entire G7. It is the first time, in history, that a pontiff participates in the work of the Group of 7 and the Holy Father will do it in the 'outreach' session, that open also to the invited countries and not only to the members of the G7. I am convinced that the presence of His Holiness will make a decisive contribution to the definition of a regulatory, ethical and cultural framework to artificial intelligence", concludes Meloni.&nbsp;
